Kinder Brownie Tart🍫 this one is definitely for the chocolate lovers! #dolcebakes | 

TART SHELL: 
.5 cup almond flour
2 3/4 cup flour
1 1/4 cup powdered sugar 
1 tsp salt
3/4 cup butter
2 eggs

BROWNIE:
1 box brownie mix
4 kinder bueno bars + minis to decorate

TO DECORATE: 
1 cup whipped cream
1/4 cup powdered sugar 
2 tbsp cream cheese 
(Add more sugar if you’d like it sweeter)

Combine the dry ingredients and butter into a food processor. Once it had a sand like consistency, add in the 2 eggs until it fully comes together. 
Refrigerate the tart dough in plastic wrap for at least 2 hours. 

Preheat oven to 350F. 
Once chilled, roll out thin and add to your tart pan. I baked mine with ceramic beads so the center doesn’t rise, but you could also use beans! Bake for 12 minutes. Prepare the brownie Batter while you wait. 

Follow the instructions on the brownie box and add in the kinder bueno bars. 

Once the tart shell is done (not fully baked), add in the brownie batter and bake for another 35-40 minutes or until the brownie is fudge and the tart shell is golden brown. Allow the tart to fully cool before decorating. Enjoy! :)

Baklava Inspired Pastries🫶🏻✨ #dolcebakes 

RECIPE:
INGREDIENTS 
1 package puff pastry sheets
1 egg + little bit of water 
1.5 cups heavy cream
3/4 cup powdered sugar
1 tsp vanilla extract

1/2 cup Pistachios blended or chopped finely
1 cup walnuts
1 tbsp cinnamon 
2 tbsp sugar
1 tbsp butter 

…….
-preheat your oven to 385 degrees
-cut puff pastry sheets in half. If you have larger sheets, cut them into rectangles or whatever shape you’d like.
-use a fork to poke holes into the cut puff pastry sheets
-brush with egg/water mix and bake for 20 min at 385F or until golden brown.

-in a food processor or blender add the walnuts, pistachios, sugar, and cinnamon and pulse. After it looks like wet sand, add a tablespooon of butter and continue to pulse until you get a thick paste. 

-combine heavy cream, powdered sugar, and vanilla into a bowl and whip until you get stiff peaks. 

-take a spooonful of whipped cream and fold it into the paste to make it lighter. 

-once the puff pastry sheets are completely cool, fill them with the nut paste, cream, and sprinkle the crushed pistachios on top. Sandwich the other half of the puff pastry. 

-dust with powdered sugar & enjoy!

Brioche Tiramisu Donuts 🤍 I love ANYTHING tiramisu flavored and these brioche tiramisu donuts are out of this world. #dolcebakes 

INGREDIENTS:
brioche dough: -1 cup lukewarm milk -2 1/4 tsp yeast -2 eggs -4 1/2 cups flour (all purpose) -1/4 cup sugar -1 tsp salt salt -6 tbsp unsalted butter melted -1/4 tsp cinnamon

filling + toppings
-2 cups heavy cream
-4oz mascarpone cream
-1/4 cup sugar 
-2 tbsp instant coffee 
-sugar / cocoa powder / cinnamon for rolling the doughnut

-oil for frying

PROCESS:
I used a kitchen aid to make the dough, it’s much faster but not necessary. You could knead it all by hand. 

-add the milk, melted butter, and yeast & set aside.

-combine flour, sugar, salt, and cinnamon. while mixing, add the milk mixture to the dry ingredients I used the dough attachment for 2-3 minutes. 
-add the eggs one at a time and continue beating until the dough starts to pull away from the side of the bowl.

-add the dough ball into an oiled bowl and set aside to rise with a kitchen towel on top. This should take about 1-1.5 hours.

-kneed the dough and roll it out. use a cookie cutter or cup to cut the donuts. 

-place the donuts on a lined baking sheet & let them rise for another half hour. while they are rising, whip together the ingredients for the filling until you have stiff peaks.

-add 3-4 inches of oil into a pan and heat. You’re looking for 350F, if the oil is too hot the outside will cook faster than the inside. drop in your donuts, and flip after 2-3 minutes.

-place them on a cooling rack to cool.

assembly:
-combine sugar, cocoa powder, cinnamon in a dish. Use this to coat your donuts. add the coffee whipped cream into a piping bag.

-pipe in the whipped cream and sprinkle with instant coffee for that classic tiramisu look!

Enjoy!🤍

Churros!🤍 A classic that’s actually so easy to make. I was going for a twisted look and I think they look a little like shrimp🫣🍤

RECIPE:
churro dough:
-1/2 cup butter 
-1 cup water
-1 tsp vanilla extract 
-1 1/4 cup flour
-pinch of salt
-1 tsp cinnamon 
-3 eggs

-vegetable oil for frying 

coating:
1/2 cup sugar
2 tsp cinnamon

chocolate sauce: 
-1 cup heavy cream
-1/2 cup chocolate chips 

process:
-combine butter, water, vanilla extract and bring to a boil. 
-remove from heat once boiled.
-add the flour, salt, and cinnamon into the wet mixture and store until it “dries up” / comes together as a ball of dough.
-allow it to cool before mixing in eggs, one at a time. make sure your dough isn’t too hot (you don’t want scrambled eggs!)
-you know it’s ready when the mixture is runny and ribbons back into the bowl. 

-heat vegetable oil in a pot. 

-add to a piping bag with a tip. 
-pipe into hot oil and flip after 2-3 minutes. once golden brown, they are done.

-combine the sugar and cinnamon & coat each churro in it. 

-for chocolate sauce, heat heavy cream and then add chocolate chips. stir well to combine & pour into a serving dish. if it’s too thick, don’t be afraid to add more heavy cream to thin it out.

Enjoy!🤍

Date Coffee Cake🤍 recipe down below! #dolcebakes 
-
recipe: 
date mix:
-1 1/4 cups boiling water 
-2 tbsp instant coffee
-10-12 dates
-1 tsp baking soda

batter:
-1 3/4 cups flour
-1/2 cup brown sugar
-1/2 cup white sugar
-1 tsp baking soda
-pinch salt
-2/3 cup butter
-1 tsp vanilla extract
-2 eggs

streusel topping
-1/3 cup brown sugar
-1/2 cup flour
-3 tbsp softened butter

process:
-pit the dates & sprinkle over the baking soda
-combine the boiling water and instant coffee
-pour over the dates and set aside for 15 min
-after 15 minutes, blend the entire mixture in the blender.

combine all the batter ingredients and the blended date mixture, give it a good mix and pour into a greased loaf pan.

combine the streusel ingredients and top the coffee cake batter with it.

bake @ 350 for 50-60 minutes.

Enjoy!🤍

Lemon Blueberry Loaf 🍋🫐☀️ I wasn’t going to post the recipe (hence the video🥲) but it was too good not to share!! This is perfect for those who don’t love overly sweet desserts. 

loaf:
3/4 cup sugar
1/2 stick unsalted butter (softened)
1/2 cup sour cream or labne 
1 egg
Juice of 1 lemon 
1.5 cups flour
2 tsp baking powder
1/2 salt
1/2 cup almond or whole milk
2 ish cups or 1 large pint of blueberries 

crumb topping:
1/2 cup flour
1/2 cup unsalted butter (softened)
1/4 cup sugar

simple glaze 
1 cup powdered sugar
2ish tbsp water 

process:
-preheat oven to 375F. 
-cream the sugar, butter, egg, lemon juice, and sour cream until smooth. 
-whisk together the dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, salt)
-alternate between the dry ingredients and milk until the batter is smooth
-add 2 tbsp of flour to the blueberries and add half inside the batter. 
-fold together and pour it into a greased loaf pan.
-sprinkle the remaining blueberries on top

-for the crumble, add the flour, sugar, and butter to a bowl and mix until crumbly.
-sprinkle on top & bake for about 1 hour and 5 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean

-mix together powdered sugar & water for the glaze. add less water for a thicker glaze.

-once the loaf is slightly cooled, drizzle the glaze on top & enjoy!🫶🏻

Rising Sun Matcha Latte | I got so many questions when I posted this to my story!! Its my version of the Rising Sun Matcha Latte from Urth Cafe. 

Its *pretty* close to the actual drink, I just skip the cocoa powder on top. 

I uses about 1.5 scoops of matcha and about a 1/4 cup of water & whisk together. Then I make a single shot of espresso and stick it in the freezer for a few minutes to cool down. Then I added ice, almond milk, a few pumps on vanilla sweetener, and Hershey chocolate syrup. Once the shot is cooled add it on top & the drink is done! #dolcebakes |
